xmlGlossaryData += '                <div class=\"GlossaryPageDefinition\" id=\"MCDropDownBody_855183615_61\" style=\"display: none;\">A Fire Behavior Prediction System (FBPS) uses one or more fire behavior fuel models. A fire behavior fuel model describes how fire is likely to behave based on natural fuel conditions. Using Rothermel\'s 1972 seminal work, Anderson (1982) originally described 13 fire behavior fuel models. Later, Scott and Burgan (2005) added 40 more fire behavior fuel models.</div>';
